The following shows a number of use cases of these params: State Apply: Param values must be known, and Peace should pass concrete values to the Item::{state_current, state_goal, apply} functions. State Discovery (fallible): Param values may be known, if predecessors have previously executed. try_state_current: StateDiscoverCmd::current e.g. Look up file contents on a remote host: match params_partial.dest_ip() { Some(dest_ip) => Some(file_hash(dest_ip, path)), None => None, // or `Some(FileState::None)`
} try_state_goal: StateDiscoverCmd::goal e.g. Look up source file contents: match params_partial.src_path() { Some(src_path) => file_hash(src_path), None => None, // or `Some(FileState::None)`
}

